TY  - JOUR
AU  - Schwert, G. William
T1  - Stock Volatility and the Crash of ’87
PY  - 1990
Y1  - 1990/01/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/3.1.77
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 3
IS  - 1
SP  - 77
EP  - 102
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - This article analyzes the behavior of stock return volatility using daily data from 1885 through 1988. The October 1987 stock market crash was unusual in many ways. October 19 was the largest percentage change in market value in over 29,000 days. Stock volatility jumped dramatically during and after the crash. Nevertheless, it returned to lower, more normal levels more quickly than past experience predicted. I use data on implied volatilities from call option prices and estimates of volatility from futures contracts on stock indexes to confirm this result.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/3.1.77
ER  - 



